# Model Training with CPCV & Production Gates

When adding or retraining machine learning models, always utilize the `CombinatorialPurgedKFold` for cross-validation. This ensures robust out-of-sample performance evaluation by testing across multiple time-period combinations with proper purging and embargo to prevent data leakage. Models must meet the project's production gate criteria, including minimum Sharpe ratio, worst-5% Sharpe, and feature importance stability, as defined in `trainer.py` (e.g., `PROD_GATE_P_SHARPE`, `PROD_GATE_SHARPE_TARGET`, `PROD_GATE_WORST5PCT`). Implement early stopping for gradient boosting models and use class weighting for imbalanced datasets.
